<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-982-730  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 982 730  OV: 07 982 478.andO; </DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Dec 18 1989 v11 n51 p61(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System Sleuth 2.0b. (Software Review) (one of eight evaluations ofdiagnostic and data-recovery utilities) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bigley, Tom; Kvitka, Andre; Eckert, Jeff.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>System Sleuth 2.0b, which lists for $149, tells a user exactlywhat components are in his system and disk drives.andP;  The programindicates the type of processor in the system, the type ofcoprocessor, the number of addressable ports, the amount and typesof memory, and versions of any memory managers that are installed.andO;System Sleuth will disclose extensive information about a harddisk.andP;  It includes many useful utilities.andP;  For example, theprogram will identifying bad tracks on a hard disk and will writethis report to a root directory on a hard drive.andP;  A more unusualfeature is the program's ability to check whether expanded memoryis working properly.andP;  The manual supplies much helpfulinformation, though it lacks an index and a glossary.andP;  SystemSleuth is a simple, easy-to-learn program.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   TouchStone Software Corp. (products).andO;Product:   System Sleuth 2.0b (Performance analysis software).andO;Topic:     DiagnosticsUtility ProgramsSoftware PackagesEvaluationDisk-Tape File UtilitiesFile Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>